fault="NO"><biblScope type="numbers">9408</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="DDbDP" default="NO"><series>0001</series>; <biblScope type="volume">3</biblScope>; <biblScope type="numbers">908</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref type="Perseus" href="0001;3;908" evaluate="all" from="ROOT" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.9408" type="bibliography" subtype="illustrations" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>keine</p></div><div n="meta.9408" type="history" subtype="locations" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p><placeName type="ancientFindspot" cert="high" full="yes">Ptolemais Euergetis</placeName> (<geogName type="nome" cert="high" full="yes">Arsinoites</geogName>), <geogName type="ancientRegion" key="Aegyptus" cert="high" full="yes">Egypt</geogName></p></div><div n="tran.9408" type="translation" lang="de" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>
            <milestone unit="line" n="1"/><app type="BGU"><lem>An <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Messius Audax, den</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app> 
            <app type="BGU"><lem><term lang="la" target="hekatontarches"><foreign lang="la">centurio</foreign></term></lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81. </bibl></wit></app>,
            <milestone unit="line" n="2" rend="break"/>von ***, Sohn des Apo[llô]nios, und A[pol]lôn[i]os, Sohn des Chairas, und 
            A[m]mônios, Sohn des Arabiôn, und [.]ariôn, Sohn des Chairas, und Euangelos, Sohn des 
            Euangelos, und Dios, Sohn eines anderen Euangelos, und [P]tolemaios, Sohn des 
            Apollônios, und Ptolemaios, Sohn des S[a]mbas, und Maximus, Sohn des Apollônios, von den 
            (Leuten) aus der <term target="metropolis">Metropole</term>. <milestone unit="line" n="8"/>Im 
            gegenwärtigen <app type="BGU"><lem>5. Jahr</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app> des Traianus Caesar, des 
            Herren,<app type="BGU"><lem> wurden</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app> wir zusammen mit anderen, die auch 
            aus der <term target="metropolis">Metropole</term> stammen, 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>in beleidigender Weise</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app> für die 
            <term target="sitologos">Sitologie</term> des Dorfes Bakchias 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>vorgeschlagen</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app>. <milestone unit="line" n="12"/><app type="BGU"><lem>Weil wir 
                wegen dieser Sache keine Ruhe finden konnten, haben wir uns an Dich 
                gewandt</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app> und Du hast uns angewiesen, nach 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>Alexandria</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app> zu reisen *** <milestone unit="line" n="15"/>und 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>so</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app> nicht 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>ausreichen wird</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 81</bibl></wit></app> *** <milestone unit="line" n="16"/>wandten wir uns 
            in Alexandria an den <term target="hegemon">Statthalter</term> Minicius Italus, den 
            <term lang="la" target="hokratistos"><foreign lang="la">vir egregius</foreign></term>. <milestone unit="line" n="18"/>Er verwies 
            uns an den hier unter ihm abzuhaltenden <term target="dialogismos">Konvent</term>. 
            <milestone unit="line" n="20"/>[Die] 
            <app><lem><seg cert="low" part="N">staatlichen</seg></lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app> <term target="sitologos">Sitologen</term> 
            <app><lem><seg cert="low" part="N">des Dorfes</seg></lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app> aber beendeten ihr 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>beleidigendes Verhalten</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82</bibl></wit></app> gegen uns nicht, sondern 
            drangen ganz ohne Befugnis mit dem 
            <term lang="la" target="archephodos"><foreign lang="la">archephodos</foreign></term> des Dorfes in die uns im 
            Dorf gehörenden Häuser ein. <milestone unit="line" n="25"/>Dabei brachen sie die Türen einiger Häuser auf und 
            bei einigen versiegelten sie <app type="BGU"><lem>&lt;die&gt;</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82</bibl></wit></app> 
            Vorratsräume, weil sie den Fehlbetrag <app type="BGU"><lem>der</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82</bibl></wit></app> 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>Sitologie</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82</bibl></wit></app>, <app><lem><seg cert="low" part="N">den</seg></lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app> wir nicht 
            übernommen haben, eintreiben wollten. <milestone unit="line" n="28"/>Hiermit ersuchen wir darum, uns, wenn es 
            Dir gefällt, zu gestatten, uns von ihnen fernzuhalten, bis 
            <app type="BGU"><lem><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> der</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82</bibl></wit></app> 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>Statthalter</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82. </bibl></wit></app>, 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>der</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82</bibl></wit></app> 
            <app type="BGU"><lem><term lang="la" target="hokratistos"><foreign lang="la">vir egregius</foreign></term></lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82. </bibl></wit></app><app type="BGU"><lem>, 
                in der Gegend eintrifft und uns anhört</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 82</bibl></wit></app>.
        </p></div><div n="tran.9408" type="translation" lang="en" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>
            <milestone unit="line" n="1"/>[To – – –] Messius Audax, 
            <app type="BGU"><lem><term lang="la" target="hekatontarches"><foreign lang="la">centurio</foreign></term></lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I 81. </bibl></wit></app>,
            <milestone unit="line" n="2" rend="break"/>[from NN], son of Apo[llo]nios and A[pol]lon[i]os, son of Chairas, and 
            A[m]monios, son of Arabion and [.]arion, son of Chairas, and Euangelos, son of Euangelos, and 
            Dios, son of another Euangelos, and [P]tolemaios, son of Apollonios, and Ptolemaios, son of 
            S[a]mbas, and Maximus, son of Apollonios, of those from the 
            <term target="metropolis">metropolis</term>. <milestone unit="line" n="8"/>In the present year 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>5</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I 81</bibl></wit></app> of Traianus Caesar, the lord, we along with others, 
            who are also from the <term target="metropolis">metropolis</term>, 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>were nominated in an insulting manner</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I 81</bibl></wit></app> for the office of 
            <term lang="la" target="sitologos"><foreign lang="la">sitologos</foreign></term> of the village of Bakchias. 
            <milestone unit="line" n="12"/><app type="BGU"><lem>As we could not find any rest concerning this, we 
                petitioned you</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I 81</bibl></wit></app> and you ordered us to journey to 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>Alexandria</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I 81</bibl></wit></app> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> will not 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>be sufficient in this way</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I 81</bibl></wit></app> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <milestone unit="line" n="16"/>we 
            petitioned the <term target="hegemon">prefect</term>, Minicius Italus, 
            <term lang="la" target="hokratistos"><foreign lang="la">vir egregius</foreign></term>, in Alexandria. 
            <milestone unit="line" n="18"/>He sent us to 
            the <term lang="la" target="dialogismos"><foreign lang="la">conventus</foreign></term>, which is due to take place 
            here under him. 
            <milestone unit="line" n="20"/>The state <term lang="la" target="sitologos"><foreign lang="la">sitologoi</foreign></term> of the 
            village did not 
